profile:
Save thousands by dealing directly with a manufacturer! Canadian Choice Windows and Doors Inc. is a leading manufacturer of windows in Canada, serving Ontario. Canadian Choice Windows and Doors offers a huge selection of replacement windows including energy efficient windows, vinyl windows, casement windows, awning windows and bow and bay windows.

Canadian Choice Windows and Doors has been serving Toronto, Richmond Hill, North York, Markham, Mississauga, Oakville, Burlington, Hamilton, Kitchener, Cambridge, Niagra Falls and the surrounding areas as well as in Calgary, Edmonton, Winnipeg and Northern Ontario. 

Why is Canadian Choice Windows and Doors your best solution for window replacement?

1. No Pressure Estimate: take your time & make informed decision

2. Save Money: Energy Star windows will reduce your energy bill by 30 %

3. Professional Installation: flawless installation and thorough clean up by courteous installers

4. High Quality: The highest quality windows in the industry, featuring foam injected honey comb structure.
 
5. Easy Financing: Financing solutions to fit anyone’s lifestyle

6. Maximum Comfort: low-E coating to reflect summer sun and retain winter heat with our Cardinal Smart Glass system.

7. Zero Maintenance: our windows are easy to clean from within the home and will never fade or discolor

Canadian Choice Windows and Doors is your smartest solution for window and door replacement.

profile:
Aeroseal Tech specializing in Aeroseal Technology and other ways  to improve Air Quality, Air Volume and Velocity for residential and commercial buildings. We take on jobs ranging from simple to complicated and perform all work with the utmost attention to detail and customer service. This way we are able to achieve the best results for our customers which we guarantee for 10 years!
Aeroseal Duct Sealing is a patented breakthrough technology that tackles leaks from the inside out. Aeroseal software allows the technician to accurately measure the duct leakage in residential homes and commercial buildings. The Aeroseal process puts escaping air under pressure and causes polymer particles to stick first to the edges of a leak, then to each other until the leak is closed.

The technology was developed within the Indoor Environment Program at Lawrence Berkeley National Laboratory, whose IAQ scientists tested it. The research was funded by US Environmental protection agency, US dept. of Energy, Electric Power Research Institute and California Institute of Energy and Environment.

The University of California was granted initial patents in 1996 and 1999, and Aeroseal holds an exclusive license to the technology.

Breathe Easy. We Are Here for All Your Heating & Cooling Needs!

There are many reasons to confidently choose Aire Serv as your provider of heater and air conditioning services—both commercial and residential. With more than 200 locations throughout the United States and Canada, Aire Serv is a trusted name in the field of heating and air conditioning installation, maintenance, and repair. We are proud of our reputation for putting clients first and getting the job done right the first time, every time.

Aire Serv of Vaughan is committed to delivering the right AC and heating system services at the right prices. We do not rush through our work and make subpar results. Our professional service technicians take the time to perform each job 100% accurately and to the utmost industry standards of quality, maximizing the value you get out of your dollars.


We Offer 24 / 7 Emergency Service

When your AC goes out in a heat wave or your furnace breaks down in an ice storm, you need emergency service fast! Rest assured and know that Aire Serv is there for you, 24 hours a day, 7 days a week, with live dispatchers, prompt service, and no charge for overtime, weekends, and holidays. It’s good to know Aire Serv is always just a phone call away!

profile:
Our Mission at Schomberg Sheet Metal is to improve the quality of life for our customers, employees, suppliers and communities through our passion for serving others. For over 30 years our family owned and operated company has continued to provide exceptional levels of service to Greater Toronto and South Simcoe regions.

Our passion for serving others begins with a passion for what we do. Each member of our dedicated team takes great pride in their craft, whether they are working on furnace repairs, or air conditioner installations. All our technicians continue to sharpen their skills with specialized training. We are committed to adding value to our customers, from helping demystify government rebates to offering expert advice and taking time to explain how products work in your home.

Our philosophy is different from other HVAC companies: because we are family-owned we treat our customers as such and each job is handled with the expert care as if it were our own home. We believe in working hard to earn our customers trust and keeping it.

profile:
About Us
For more than 20 years, PHD Plumbing, Heating and Drain has been a trusted plumbing company in the communities of Alliston, Innisfil, Cookstown, Tottenham, New Tecumseth, Barrie and Newmarket. Since our inception in 2000, we have been recognized for our integrity, service and hard work as we have delivered a large range of residential and commercial projects to several satisfied customers.

We pride ourselves in arriving to the job site on time, prepared and paying attention to our customer concerns and requirements. We are committed to stand by our reputation which has been crafted on superior customer service, workmanship and experience.

Our team of licensed plumbers strive to provide long lasting customer relationships and make every effort to exceed our customers’ expectations by providing honest, fair, knowledgeable and professional services each and every time we work on a project.

If you are a homeowner or a commercial business that is experiencing problems with your plumbing, don’t hesitate to call us today to schedule a service. From blocked drains, drain repair, to emergency plumbing services, we are devoted to provide quick and efficient services at affordable prices. Leave it to PHD Plumbing, Heating and Drain to provide you with an effective solution to your plumbing related issues.

Call the professionals at PHD Plumbing today to see how we can help you with your plumbing situation. At PHD Plumbing, Heating and Drain, we understand emergencies can happen at any time of the day and for this reason we provide 24/7 emergency plumbing services to our community.

profile:
What Can I Expect As A Lake Simcoe Heating & Air Conditioning Customer?
Fast, friendly service, 7 days a week!

We are open Monday through Friday, 8am to 5pm. We also have 24-hour emergency service.

We are proud to service Barrie and the surrounding areas including: Innisfil, Oro, Orillia, Wasaga Beach and Stayner.

Service on all brands and models
We service and repair all brands of air conditioners, gas furnaces, heat pumps and mini splits. Our fully-stocked truck carry hundred of parts. Most times we have the part you need on the truck and are able to fix your problem the same day.

New Systems Installed Right
The most important day in the life of your air conditioner, furnace or heat pump is the day it’s installed. Most equipment failure can be traced to an improper installation.

Your heating and cooling system is made up of four components. Only one component, the equipment, is controlled by the manufacturer. The other three components; the refrigerant charging, the electrical power supply, and the ducted air supply and distribution system are all the responsibility of the contractor you choose.

Ardent Heating, Air Conditioning & Water Treatment Specialists are celebrating 10 years in business in 2013! We are located in Barrie, Ontario and we serve all the surrounding communities such as Innisfil, Oro, Shanty Bay, Angus, Spring Water, Hawkestone and Cookstown. 
 
We sell, service, repair and install all types of heating for the home or light commercial such as furnaces, fireplaces, tankless water heaters, space heaters and commercial roof top units. 
We also sell service and install central air conditioning, ductless split systems and heat pumps.
 
Our water division will help you with your water treatment needs, including water softeners for treatment of hard water, iron filters, bacteria filters, water purifiers and Reverse Osmosis systems.
 
Ardent has a very good reputation for good, fast and honest service. Barrie and surrounding area residents know they can trust Ardent Heating, Air Conditioning & Water Treatment Specialists to get the job done in a professional manner & we will do it right.

profile:
We are a family owned, now 3rd generation Heating & Air Conditioning business. With A little over 75 years combined experience. 

How it all started. At the age of 16 my father entered trade school and worked on site with a qualified technician during the evenings and weekends.

In 1966 he passed his Gas Fitters license and 4 years later qualified for his Oil Burner license.
2 years later he stared his own business Industrial Heating and Air Conditioning which he 
ran until 1989.  He closed the company for personal health reason and move to B.C.

In 1992 he returned to Toronto and upgraded his present licenses to Gas Fitter #1 and Oil Burner Technician 1, from there he started “Anything Gas” in 1993. 

He upgraded the company to offer more products and services in 2002 with his wife Penny
Under the name Anything gas/billpenny ltd. I joined my father as a service technician in 1995 until he decided to retire in January 2018. At that time, I took over the company under Anything Gas/Master Mechanical Ltd. 

My father is still around in advisory position.  I was always taught to do it right the first time as it saves you time and problems in the long run.

We still run the business with the same pride and professionalism as my father has done.
We are now on our 3rd generation,teaching my son to do the same.

Aeroseal Plus specializing in Aeroseal Technology to improve Home Comfort and Indoor Air Quality for residential homes.
Aeroseal Duct Sealing is a patented breakthrough technology that tackles leaks from the inside out. The Aeroseal process puts escaping air under pressure and causes polymer particles to stick first to the edges of a leak, then to each other until the leak is completely sealed.
For more info please visit aerosealplus.ca

profile:
Running into an issue with your home’s heating or cooling system is inconvenient and can often lead to discomfort if the problem isn’t taken care of right away. At Southern Comfort HVAC in Barrie, Ontario, we’re here to help. Due to our varied selection of HVAC services, we guarantee that we can resolve any issue you are experiencing with your HVAC system. Additionally, each of our certified technicians is highly customer-oriented and dedicated to doing the job right the first time. If you need someone to take care of a heating or cooling problem in your home, turn to us at Southern Comfort HVAC.

Contact us at Southern Comfort HVAC to learn about our central air conditioners and get your free estimate. We can make sure your home stays at the perfect cool temperature all summer long!

Our duct work installation and services are efficient, timely and high quality. If the duct work in your home was not installed or sealed properly, you could be losing up to 20% of the hot and cold air your HVAC system puts out. If you’re paying too much for electricity, your duct work is making strange noises, or some rooms are colder/hotter than others, give us a call for a duct work inspection.

We truly understand how important it is to listen to you in order to determine your unique needs. We know that every customer is different, and that a "one-size-fits-all" approach is not the answer.
